rComments: A genuinely nice professor! Makes you feel good after each lecture and is not a hard marker, nor are the tests and the assignments difficult.

You can just tell that the Prof really loves what he teaches. He is engaging in class with relevant personal anecdotes and public examples, makes sure what we learn is important and interesting, and integrates many types of media to ensure our understanding of material. He's very approachable, accessible, and treats us as peers. Best prof I've had.

Hoselton's one of the reasons I decided to stay in school. He doesn't know it, and I didn't go to office hours, or answer all the questions no one else would but he's the only prof who made me feel like my hard work and dedication meant something to him besides a number on a piece of paper. He gives you real answers, with fun insights to his life.

Amazing , funny and engaging. One of the best professors I've ever had. His lectures are fun and he encourages participation. He makes difficult topics easy to understand. It is sad that he will be retiring this year because more students need to take his courses!

Hoselton's lectures and assignments are very clear, he takes the time to organize things in a way that's easy to understand. Content is very easy and marks are generally good. He makes himself very accessible to students outside of class as well as before and after. If you ask for clarification, he will make sure 100% that you understand.

Professor Hoselton is an excellent educator. His lectures are clear, organized, and easy to follow. He invites class discussion and respects each student's input and perspective. His assignments and tests are clearly outlined and he dedicates ample time in class to discuss the parameters, expectations, and grading. He's simply amazing!
Clear lectures, and a very engaging professor. Step aside David Perley (though you still are one of the best), Steve Hoselton is the new Based God.

Steve is a very responsible instructor that I would definitely take his course again if get a chance. His lectures are clear and succinct, the tests are not hard. The content of the course is interesting!

Professor Hoselton is really responsible for students who take his course. He answers every question thoroughly in class or after class. He is humorous.  His lectures are inspiring, not boring at all! Highly recommend his course to students in Book and Media Studies!!

Amazing professor and human being. Definitely changed the way I see mass media. Assignments were laid out very clearly with plenty of in lecture instruction on how to do well in them. Very intelligent, kind, and CUTE!
AMAZING. By far the best prof I've ever had. Really cares about you and the class he is teaching. Whenever I see he is teaching a course, I take it.

By far one of the most amazing professors I have ever had. He is absolutely hilarious (DON'T miss out on his lectures!), creates a laid-back environment that encourages lively discussions and is extremely helpful with any questions pertaining to assignments. Courseload is spread evenly. Such a great experience I plan to take more of his courses.

Steve Hoselton is a wonderful man and by far one of the most inspiring teachers I've had in my life. He grades very fairly, and is always extremely helpful and flexible with students. Steve is easily one of the reasons why U of T has the reputation it does, he is an amazing professor and human being.
Hoselton is amazing! So personable, he really cares about each student. He understands the challenges of university completely and tries to help students overcome these obstacles.

Steve is amazing! He genuinely cares for his students and makes a point of teaching life skills--not just course content. His lectures are funny and you get to leave class 5-10 min. His synthesis classes are great and really show that he cares what students think about the content. If you go to lectures, you will do well. Easy A.
Amazing Prof! Very patient and Kind!

Professor Hoselton is a treasure for St. Michael's College and the University of Toronto. The assignments were spread out nicely throughout the term, which is good, as the workload in other courses are generally already heavy. His assessment on assignments were fair. Additionally, he is a very approachable and helpful instructor.
